@startuml
state "Inventory" as Inventory
state "Add Goods" as AddGoods
state "Update Price" as UpdatePrice
state "Remove Goods" as RemoveGoods
state "Expired Goods" as ExpiredGoods
state "Place Order" as PlaceOrder
state "Generate Invoice" as GenerateInvoice
state "Search Items" as SearchItems
state "Calculate Discount and Tax" as CalculateDiscountTax
state "Generate Receipt" as GenerateReceipt
state "Replace Item" as ReplaceItem
state "Cancel Receipt" as CancelReceipt
state "Record Customer Request" as RecordCustomerRequest
state "View Summary Report" as ViewSummaryReport

Inventory [*] --> AddGoods : add new goods to the inventory
AddGoods --> Inventory : save added goods
Inventory [*] --> UpdatePrice : update price of existing items in the inventory
UpdatePrice --> Inventory : save updated price
Inventory [*] --> RemoveGoods : remove goods from the inventory that are no longer required
RemoveGoods --> Inventory : save removed goods
Inventory [*] --> ExpiredGoods : identify expired goods and notify user about their removal
ExpiredGoods --> Inventory : save removed expired goods
Inventory [*] --> PlaceOrder : place an order to a supplier for additional goods when required
PlaceOrder --> GenerateInvoice : generate invoice once order is placed
GenerateInvoice --> Inventory : save generated invoice
Inventory [*] --> SearchItems : search for items available in the inventory and select them for purchase
SearchItems --> CalculateDiscountTax : calculate applicable discount and tax based on selected items
CalculateDiscountTax --> GenerateReceipt : generate receipt for customer after purchase
GenerateReceipt --> Inventory : save generated receipt
Inventory [*] --> ReplaceItem : replace an item or cancel receipt during billing process if needed
ReplaceItem --> CancelReceipt : cancel receipt
CancelReceipt --> Inventory : save cancelled receipt
Inventory [*] --> RecordCustomerRequest : record customer requests for items that may not be currently available
RecordCustomerRequest --> ViewSummaryReport : view summary report of all transactions carried out in the system at any point
ViewSummaryReport --> Inventory : save viewed summary report

@enduml
